cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of 3D shape reconstruction from images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method proposed in the paper involves embedding pixels onto a unit hemisphere, which is a geometric representation (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the use of manifold learning methods, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). The approach presented in the paper is based on a novel embedding method, which involves mapping pixels to normals on the unit hemisphere, and this involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve the reconstruction of objects from images, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
